         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ A copy of my former report to the previous Minister of the Department, who has ¶  ¶ already delt ¶ dealt. ¶ with ¶  ¶ this case is respectfully again submitted, and now also a statement of the arti...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.08.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James Casey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">72/17705, unit 365, VPRS 44/P inward registered and unregistered correspondence, VA 538 Department of Crown Lands and Survey, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A copy of my former report to the previous Minister of the Department, who has<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">already delt</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>dealt.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                  <hi rend="underline">with</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>this case is respectfully again submitted, and now also a statement of the artisan Cottrell, correcting the assertions of the Carpenter Petersen.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to C. Duffy, 18 November 1871, a copy of which (in G. Luehmann's handwriting) is attached to the file, together with H. Petersen's renewed complaint dated 20 August 1872 to the Minister of Lands, J. Casey, concerning M's alleged injustice towards him, and a statement dated 24 August 1874 signed 'Sam Cottrell', setting out the work Cottrell normally did in the Garden, that Petersen claimed he should have been employed to do but that Cottrell said was not of a kind that required<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the attention of a trained carpenter. The latter carries an annotation by M: 'The wages of Artisan Cottrell are<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">considerably less</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>than those of an ordinary Carpenter FvM 24/8/72.'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The hon. the Minister will kindly observe, that since 1870 I have<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">no funds</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to employ a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">regular Carpenter</hi>
               </seg>, that the man Petersen was engaged at<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">weekly warning</hi>
               </seg>, that he has<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">no claims</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on the Department, that he is quite able to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">obtain employment elsewhere</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in his trade, that he is quite fit to work, and that any supposed injury to his sight arose, if really such took place, entirely out of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">incautiousness of his own</hi>
               </seg>.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. McCulloch, 3 October 1870, where M commented on Petersen's complaints of poor eyesight<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>being caused by his employment<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at the Botanic Garden.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Direct. botan. Garden</p>
            <p rend="Normal"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">24/8/72.</p>
         </div>
